DESCRIPTION: Autopilot processor for autonomous flight, GPS modlue to allow autonomous navigation, and radio modules to send back data like location, speed, battery etc
First person view goggles to see from the plane's perspective- necessary for locating lost hikers
Highly recommended so the plane can adapt the power in the motor/angle of flaps to the wind speed.
Small motor that can turn to a specific angle depending on voltage. This is used to steer the plane by moving the flaps.
Electronic speed controller. Controls the speed of the motor by varying current going to it.
Controller sends radio signals to the reciever in order to control the plane by changing the current given to the motor and servos.
A Lithium polymer battery is essential to power the plane. It is useful due it's versatility and being light-weight.
